This paper is about improving the performance of Web search ranking models, which falls under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also discusses machine learning techniques such as model interpolation and boosting, which are commonly used in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques that are relevant to Web search ranking. Finally, the paper discusses the use of tree-based models, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) applications.
